From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Quenchforge Contributors <maintainers@cerid-ai.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 21:17:58 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] metal: default to serial dispatch on non-UMA devices

Non-UMA Metal devices (AMD discrete, Intel iGPU) have unreliable
command-buffer ordering on the concurrent-dispatch path. Reproducer
(Mac Pro 2019 + Radeon Pro Vega II): BERT-family embeddings return
cos_sim ~0.12 against a correct reference the moment concurrency is
enabled, independent of the simdgroup-reduction fallback kernels (which
were active and correct in the same measurement with concurrency off).

Default use_concurrency to false when the device lacks unified memory so
correctness does not depend on operators setting
GGML_METAL_CONCURRENCY_DISABLE; GGML_METAL_CONCURRENCY_FORCE=1 opts back
in for testing.
---
 ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-context.m | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-context.m b/ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-context.m
index 32d97cd5d..6169a7e67 100644
--- a/ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-context.m
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-metal/ggml-metal-context.m
@@ -136,6 +136,21 @@ ggml_metal_t ggml_metal_init(ggml_metal_device_t dev) {
     res->use_fusion      = getenv("GGML_METAL_FUSION_DISABLE") == nil;
     res->use_concurrency = getenv("GGML_METAL_CONCURRENCY_DISABLE") == nil;
 
+    // Quenchforge patch 0005: non-UMA Metal devices (AMD discrete, Intel iGPU)
+    // have unreliable command-buffer ordering on the concurrent-dispatch path.
+    // 60-second reproducer (Mac Pro 2019 + Vega II, 2026-07-08): BERT
+    // embeddings return cos_sim ~0.12 against a correct reference the moment
+    // concurrency is enabled — independent of the simdgroup-reduction
+    // miscompile addressed by the fallback kernels (patches 0001/0003/0004),
+    // which were active and correct in the same measurement with concurrency
+    // off. Default to serial dispatch on these devices so correctness does
+    // not depend on operators knowing an env var; opt back in for testing
+    // with GGML_METAL_CONCURRENCY_FORCE=1 (same convention as the
+    // GGML_METAL_FORCE_* gates in patch 0001).
+    if (!props_dev->has_unified_memory && getenv("GGML_METAL_CONCURRENCY_FORCE") == nil) {
+        res->use_concurrency = false;
+    }
+
     {
         const char * val = getenv("GGML_METAL_GRAPH_DEBUG");
         res->debug_graph = val ? atoi(val) : 0;
-- 
